inn1.comm: some movement for Mills, short of a good length outside off, moves away, leaves it be
goodish length this time, a hint of movement away after landing in that channel outside off, left alone
pitching it a fraction outside off, steps out and gets to the pitch and defends it into the off side
beaten this time, short of a good length outside off, pokes at it and is beaten
in that corridor again, pitching on that driving length, some shape away, leaves it be this time
bowling from wide of the crease, angling in towards middle and leg, turns it behind square for a single
bowling from slightly wide of the crease, angling in towards middle and leg, gets on the back foot, squares him up a bit, made contact with the thigh, would have probably gone over
fires it on middle, gets on the back foot, is nicely behind it, defends it to mid-on
lands on a good length, drives it firmly but Nathan McCullum at extra cover dives to his right and prevents a few runs
bowled it full on the off, defended solidly towards extra cover
short of a good length on middle, defended into the leg side off the back foot
nicely timed, pitched it up on middle but he met it with a full face, driving it uppishly but firmly past mid-on
good, sharp bouncer, dropped it short on the off and the batsman was wise to duck under it
back of a length outside off, moving away, sways out of the way does Chibhabha
short of a good length, moving away again, watches it through to the keeper
similar length and line, shortish outside off and he leaves it alone, watchful first couple of overs
slightly wide of the crease and again in that corridor outside off, shoulders arms to that one
lovely line, driving length outside off but backed up with movement, left alone once more

Sibanda poked at that one, short of a good length and this nipped away just a hint, Sibanda had been kept quiet outside off and he couldn't resist stabbing at that one, nicked it faintly to the keeper, that's his first ODI wicket
short of a good length outside off, knocked into the off side
yorker length outside off stump this time, dug out in front of square
pitched it up outside off, pushed towards mid-off, thinks of a single but Nathan McCullum doesn't allow them one
trying to tease him in that channel outside off, shoulders arms to that one
shortish on the off, rocks back and punches it towards cover, good, tight start by New Zealand
full outside off, gets to the pitch and defends it solidly towards cover
short of a good length on the off, rocks back and guides it behind point for a couple of runs, third man takes a while to run in
short of a good length outside off, holds its line this time and he leaves it be
angling in towards middle and off, covers it well and pushes it back to Mills
superbly bowled, angling in towards off and middle and nipped away lethally, got him on the back foot and he was caught in two minds, got squared up completely and was beaten

missed run-out, Guptill misses a chance, punched off the back foot towards him at cover, Chibhabha wants the single and is sent back, he slips as he turns around but Guptill doesn't hit the target, would have been out by a mile
angling in towards middle, pushed from the crease towards mid-on
gets outside the line to play that into the leg side, is struck high on the pads as he tries to turn the face
short of a good length on the off, pushes it back to the bowler
dropped it short on middle and it hurried onto him, tried to whip it off the back foot but it ended up striking him on the thigh
banged it short on middle and Maskadza, who had thought of the pull, wisely withdrew the shot and let it go

cleaned him up, the middle stump is out of the ground, drew him forward with a good length delivery this time, Masakadza was half forward as he tried to drive it through the covers, got an inside edge that knocked out middle. New Zealand continue to be impressive
Mills continues to test the batsmen outside off, has been very consistent in his line today, left alone by Chibhabha
short of a good length outside off again, doesn't want to chase it does Chibhabha, leaves it be
angling in towards middle, gets on the back foot to defend it towards mid-on
pitched up and he goes after it, drives it soundly between cover and point, Guptill gives chase but can't quite drag it back despite a full-length dive
a little more width on this one but again, it's moving further, leaves it alone this time
short of a good length on the off, defended off the back foot towards cover
angling in towards middle, gets on the back foot and turns it behind square for a single
shortish on the off, pushes him back and he meets him solidly, knocking it down towards cover

gone, Bracewell's had an excellent debut so far, teasing the batsman outside off again, moves away just a hint and it's sufficient to fetch him a wicket, it's Chibhabha's turn to play at it this time and he feathers it to Brendon McCullum
bowled full on middle, Taibu plays it from the crease and turns it away past mid-on for a single
short of a good length outside off, leaves it alone, this one holds its line
found the gap, short outside off, punched between cover and point into the deep for three runs
back of a length on middle, rocks back and defends it to the bowler
banged it short on middle, not called a wide, was a tough too high it seemed, ducked under it
full on the off, gets forward and defends it towards cover, pinches a quick single
in that channel outside off and still getting movement, shoulders arms to the keeper
fullish outside off but Taibu isn't risking driving, leaves it alone
short of a good length outside off, leaves it alone to the keeper
shortish on middle, rocks on the back foot and plays it towards mid-on
goodish length on the off, gets to the pitch and defends it down the pitch
fullish outside off, driven on the up this time towards extra cover, Nathan McCullum fumbles and concedes a single, a rare lapse in the field
fires it full on the off stump, defended it back to the bowler
tried to be a little smart there did Taylor, pretended to duck but tried to upper cut it at the same time, missed
short of a good length on middle, rocks back and taps it to the bowler
good length outside off, closer to the stumps, Taibu lets it be
a touch fuller on the off, gets forward and plays it back to the bowler
a touch short again on middle and off, gets across and tries to play it down straight, struck on the thigh
slower one this time, a touch too straight, turned away past square leg for a couple of runs
played it slightly away from his body, pushed it towards point

Kane Williamson, superbly done, pitched up and he drove it uppishly towards extra cover, Williamson didn't have a lot of reaction time there but he timed his jump perfectly and palmed it with one hand before clasping it with both on the second attempt
starts off with plenty of width, short as well and it's punished past point for a boundary
short and wide, goes for the cut again, gets a thick outside edge to third man for a single
back of a length on the off, taps it down towards point from the crease
full outside off, in the slot but Mutizwa opts to leave it alone
in that channel outside off this time, much better from McKay, left alone once more
shortish on leg stump, tries to turn it square but ends up being struck on his thigh
pitched outside leg and nipped in to catch him on the pads as he shuffled across to turn it square
bowled it full on the off, pushed down the pitch past mid-off, just the single though
short and wide, there for the taking and he goes after it, tried to slash it hard over point but missed
goodish length on middle and off this time, gets a stride out and defends it to mid-off
short of a good length on middle, nips away again and this time he's beaten as he tried to open the face
shortish, mistimed an attempt at a pull, got it wide of square leg into the deep for a couple of runs
dropped it short outside off, cut away straight to point
fired on middle, gets on the back foot and taps it in front of midwicket
drops it short outside off, plenty of width from McKay, Taylor reaches for it and finds the gap, placing it past cover
straying on leg stump this time, turned past square leg for a single
bowled it short outside off, too short and it was there to cut, Mutizwa reached for it but missed
full outside off, digs it out towards cover
angling it wide of Taylor, on a good length, he leaves it alone
pushed off the back foot into the off side
short of a good length outside off, borders on being a wide but he doesn't call it, left alone
pitched it up outside off, driven firmly through the covers into the deep for a couple of runs
banged it short on middle, well over the batsman's head, called a wide this time
plays with bat close to pad, only half-forward, gets an inside edge onto his pads and it rolls into the leg side
round the wicket this time, pitched it on a good length, pushed on the up towards cover
in that channel outside off and Mutizwa is content to let it go
short of a good length outside off, runs it down towards third man for a single
they're not chasing these tempting deliveries outside off, left alone to the keeper
reaches forward and pushes that between extra cover and mid-off for a single
short of a good length outside off, leaves it alone and it goes through to the keeper
short of a good length on the off, Taylor gets on the back foot and taps it to extra cover
gets across this time and treats it identically, straight to extra cover
the ball's still moving a bit, Franklin gets it to nip away, Taylor's not going after those
bowled it on a good length on the off, stretches forward and defends it to mid-off
slower one bowled full, pushed it wide of mid-off for a single
short ball angling in from outside off, calmly blocked.
near yorker outside off, Taylor digs it out into the covers.
over-pitched and there for the drive, but Taylor's in such a defensive mindset, understandably, that he laces it straight to cover.
slanted generously down the leg side, Taylor helps it along to fine leg for one.
where did that come from? Mutizwa breaks the shackles with the most sumptuous of pulls. He stands tall, swivels and thumps a McKay bumper high over midwicket.
slower ball pushed wide of off stump, Mutizwa lets it go.
Franklin angles one across Taylor who defends to the off side.
over-pitched outside off, Taylor pushes it straight to mid-off.
lucky. Taylor is cut in half by a polite indipper from Franklin, and ends up inside edging an attempted dab to the off side, just past the stumps and through to fine leg for four.
better from Taylor, covers the gap as he leans into a push-drive and takes a single to mid-off.
slower ball pitched up outside off, pushed gingerly into the covers.
another slower ball nips in, Mutizwa is early on the airy pull and it goes to the off side off the pad.
turns in from outside off, gets forward and pushe sit towards cover
gets forward and plays it back to the bowler
turned away off the front foot wide of square leg for a brace
tossed up outside off, driven down towards long-on for a single
flighted on the off, gets to the pitch and pushes it back to the bowler
flat outside off, shortish, punched back to the bowler
tossed up on the off, works it wide of midwicket for a single
tossed up on middle, driven down to long-on for one more
bowling round the wicket, turned it wide of square leg for a single
fires it quick on middle from round the wicket, gets on the back foot and plays it back to the bowler
played down the ground towards long-on, keeps strike
shortish outside off, rocks back and cuts it wide of point for a single in the deep
punched off the back foot towards deep cover for a single
stretches forward and pushes it towards cover
flighted on middle, long-on into the action again
Taylor times that very well, bowled flat but he came down the track and just punched it through the line uppishly past mid-off
turned it towards short fine leg, was straying down leg but couldn't beat the fielder inside the circle
tossed up on the off, crunched to extra cover
eased it through to deep cover to raise the 50-stand, the innings in a rebuilding phase here
shortish on the off, waits for it to turn in and punches it back to the bowler
full on middle, pushed back to the bowler
fetches it from outside off and sweeps it hard to square leg where the fielder fumbles and allows a single
takes it from a length and drives it to long-on to keep strike
round the wicket, bowled a little short outside off, knocks it wide of point for a single
punched to long-on off the back foot for a single
gets forward and strikes it straight to midwicket
pushed through the line towards long-on for one more
fires it short on middle, tickled wide of square leg for a single
short of a good length, turns in, waits for it and punches it to long-on
flighted outside off, drilled but there is a deep cover in place, Kane Williamson cuts it off
quicker through the air but full, Taylor chips it over the bowler's head, long-on cuts it off but they've managed to take a couple
he's timing them well, driven firmly to long-off for a single
worked away off the back foot but straight to midwicket
gets front and across and turns it to square leg
pushed through the line to long-off for a single, a decent recovery from this pair
shortish on the off, gets back and whips it past midwicket for a single
floated up on the off, played it back to the bowler
gets front and across and turns it away to midwicket
quicker this time, and straight, turned to midwicket once more
that's three consecutive deliveries that it's gone to the same fielder
plays it more square this time, past square leg, for a comfortable single
smartly done, round the wicket and he angles it towards leg stump, Mutizwa paddles it past short fine into the deep for a couple of runs
flighted on the off, driven straight back to the bowler
turns in from outside off, looks to stab it to cover, gets a thick inside edge to midwicket
goes for the paddle sweep again, plenty of vacant spaces and it allows them to come back for the second
chipped it wide of midwicket for a single
flat outside off, gets forward and pushes it to extra cover
fired in on middle and leg, he can't get it away.
this one slips down the leg side and Baz gets excited after collecting it.
Mutizwa works a single into the leg side, played easily with the turn.
full ball outside off, pushed into the covers.
Mutizwa leans out and defends a flighted delivery into the covers.
loopy ball outside off, Mutizwa is drawn into a loose drive and edges it through the vacant slips for a couple.
Nathan curls this in outside off, Taylor nudges to the leg side.
Taylor jumps out and taps towards mid-on with the spin.
close. Full and flat, lands outside off and heads on towards the stumps. Taylor misses the sweep and is struck in front. No referrals in this series ...
this one slips on the batsman and pops up on the leg side, but safely away from Nathan on his follow through.
Mutizwa hangs back and pushes a full ball into the off side.
worked with the turn to midwicket, but not for runs.
short of a length outside off, Taylor opens the face to guide it to third man.,
swing and a miss. He has a reputation for pulling well, but misses this one as it bursts through at pace. It was shot, so the shot was on.
shaped onto the pads, worked to the leg side.
length ball, Mutizwa plays a laboured haul-drive to mid-on. Needless throw hits the stumps and gives them the single.
short of a length outside off, dabbed into the covers and Taylor wants one. Mutizwa doesn't.
angled in gently towards the pads, dabbed away square for a single.
speared in full, pushed to the leg side.
Nathan clangs a return catch. It was tossed up outside off, and Taylor was drawn early into the drive. Nathan reacted well as it popped up to his left, but couldn't hold on.
Mutizwa gets a full ball on the stumps, played to the leg side.
stays back and forces a length ball into the off side.
gets the single now, driven through mid-on for a single
Fifty for Taylor, and how well he has played here. Dabs a full ball on the pads square for a single.
full ball from Mills outside off, Taylor guides it square with an angled face.
full again, Taylor drives fluently through extra cover for one more.
slow short ball, Mutizwa handles it well as he rolls the wrists over the pull shot, but the running is sluggish.
this one ducks in, Taylor drops it to mid-on for one more.
fullish ball tails into Mutizwa, who drags it away through midwicket for one.
Mills angles another one in, Taylor defends from the crease
chipped in front of midwicket
gets front and across and plays it to midwicket again
appeal for lbw, turning in from outside off, get tries to turn the face on it, gets struck on the pads but outside the line
steps out of the crease and works it away to deep midwicket for a single

dropped and six, Taylor went on the attack there, picked it up from a length and struck it flat towards long-off where Andy McKay was in place but couldn't hold on as he tried to take it over his head, ended up palming it over the ropes
short outside off, reaches to play a cut, misses
bowled it full on middle, flicked away wristily towards deep midwicket for a single
in the channel outside off stump, holds its line and he lets it through to the keeper

run-out attempt, shortish on middle, Taylor tries to work it away is struck on the rib, Mutizwa is halfway down the pitch as Taylor doesn't respond to the single, McKay picks up and throws down the stumps at the non-striker's end but Mutizwa's managed to make it back in time
shortish on middle, turned into the leg side off the back foot for a single
bowled it full on the off stump, pushes it towards mid-off
That's disappeared, flighted, tempting delivery, Taylor came down the track, got to the pitch and smashed it over long-on
bowled it on middle, tickled past square leg for a single
played down towards long-on for a single
driven down towards long-on for a single
low full toss on the off, long-on is a preferred place for scoring for this pair
pushed off the back foot towards wide long-on for one more to keep strike
short of a good length on the off, gets back and knocks it into the off side
not giving much away at all, Taylor shuffles across but has to check his shot at the end, played back to the bowler
slower one bowled short on the off, turned away past short fine leg for a couple of runs
good length on the off, defended into the off side
slower one bowled slightly short on leg stump, tries to tickle it wide of short fine, gets a leg-bye
a bit of reverse on that one, aiming for the blockhole, dug out wide of square leg for a single
angling in from round the wicket, defended in the direction of mid-off
short of a good length on middle, gets across and taps it towards midwicket
slower one and he picked it, landed on a length and he dispatched it handsomely over mid-on for a boundary
drops it past extra cover in the direction of mid-off for a single
low full toss on the off stump, pushes it straight to extra cover
almost in the blockhole, Taylor had made room to force it through the off side but missed, couldn't connect
short of a good length on middle, turned towards deep square leg for a single
low full toss outside leg stump, this with the short fine leg inside the circle, Taylor helps it on its way for four
makes room and the bowler chases him, turned past midwicket for a single
dragged it short on the off and was promptly pulled to deep midwicket, but just the single
tumbled as he delivered that ball did Bracewell, no damage done though, just defended to extra cover
he's batted beautifully, seized an opportunity again as Bracewell ended up bowling too straight, shuffled across and glanced it elegantly to the fine-leg boundary
short of a good length on the off, defended off the back foot to cover
pitched up on middle, turned wide of mid-on to complete the single and raise his half-century, this has been an excellent stand and Mutizwa has played a measured, yet crucial innings
fends that short ball wide of short fine for a single
good length on middle, defends it solidly back towards the bowler
banged it short, was the slower boucer, jabbed it behind short fine for a couple more
picked the gap, was given a bit of width, opened the face at the right time to steer it past point into the deep for three runs
pitched up on the off, drilled towards mid-on
pushed through point for a single
short of a good length on middle, turned behind square, enough tme available to come back for the second
there is a fine leg in place now, flicked uppishly towards him but just for a single
appeal for a catch, was pitched up and he tried to drive it back, got an inside edge and lobbed up off his shoe back to the bowler, it probably hit the ground before hitting the shoe
comes down the track and drives it hard back to Bracewell, it ricochets off him in the direction of long-on
driven down the ground to long-on
smacked wide of long-on but again, just the single
swung away towards deep midwicket for one more
that's powerfully struck, took it from outside off and hammered it with the turn over deep midwicket, clean strike, Zimbabwe have fought back superbly here
comes down the track to get to the pitch, pushed it to midwicket
starts off his new spell with a long hop, dragged it really short and Taylor got into position early to pull it past square leg to collect four more
defended calmly in the director of cover
short ball outside off, cracked towards deep point for a single
The pressure's back on New Zealand now, excellent improvisation, shortish on middle, he moves across and scoops it past fine leg
chased a really wide one and got a nick, pitched well outside off and would have probably bordered on being a wide had he left it alone but he went after it and edged one to the keeper
short of a good length on the off, defended in front of cover
shortish outside off, it's guided down to third man for a single
bowled it short on the off, rocks back and taps it in the direction of extra cover
banged it short outside off and he let it through to the keeper
well bowled again, quick and short outside off, Chigumbura sways out of the way
good length on the off, pushed towards cover from the crease
slower one bowled short outside off, dropped it towards point
superbly struck, right in the slot and there was enough width to free his arms, smashed it over mid-off, clean and flat
that fielder has been pushed back now, struck along the ground wide of him for a couple more
pushed off the front foot towards extra cover
slower one, tries to clear the long-off boundary but doesn't quite get hold, lands in front of long-off
fetched it from the off stump, paddling it behind short fine for a couple more runs
around a good length, gets forward and plays it towards midwicket, just the single
round the wicket, bowls a slower one full on middle, tickled down to fine leg for a single
yorker and he couldn't do much about that, tried to open the face on that one but missed it altogether, played a little inside the line as well
aiming at middle and off, and aiming for the yorker, pushed towards extra cover
played wide of point and the fielder there can't quite cover it, concedes a single after overrunning it, Ryder it was
chipped wide of midwicket to rotate the strike
edged and gone! Short of a good length, he tried to guide that past the keeper and towards third man, ended up guiding it straight to McCullum
short of a good length outside off, run down to third man for a single
a bit of width and he chops it down to third man for a single
worked away from the off towards deep square leg for a single
beaten, Mills is still getting a bit of nip, short of a good length and it squares up Utseya as he thinks of playing at it
guided wide of Taylor and he flinhs himself to his left to stop that one, prevents at least a couple of runs
knocks it down off the back foot to Taylor yet again
appeal for lbw, angling in towards off and middle and Taylor is struck on the pads as he moves across to defend, was struck outside the line
getting some reverse is Bracewell, full on the off, pushed down to long-on for a single
tries to cut a good length ball does Utseya and he makes no contact
short of a good length, defended wide of extra cover to steal a quick single
knocks it behind point, calls for a single does Taylor but doesn't get the desired response from the non-striker
Well played Brendan Taylor, shuffles across and tickles that past square leg to raise his century, he's led by example, that's his 5th ODI ton
slaps that short delivery just wide of mid-on, a fumble allows them a single, 200 up
finds the gap, short and wide and he slashes it past point, McKay runs across from third man and dives to his right to haul it in, an excellent effort
drags it from the off towards Ross Taylor at midwicket, the New Zealand captain scores a direct-hit but his counterpart has made it back, only just
short of a good length, dabbed down to third man for a single
short outside off, slapped towards deep cover for a single
dropped it short outside off, made room and failed to reach it, this has been a tidy spell from Mills
Taylor's not going to let those go, a juicy full toss on middle, he duly swings it hard and flat over the deep square leg boundary
bowls it full outside off, steers it wide of deep point for a couple of runs
a slower length ball and he picks it beautifully, gets across and lofts it clean between long-on and deep midwicket, clears the ropes
six more, Taylor's gone wild, that was a slog but an effective one, Bracewell dropped it slightly short and it was enough for Taylor to shovel it over deep square leg once again, three this over
ooh, Taylor thought that'll be given a wide but it wasn't and it was well inside that line, in the channel outside off and he let it go
bowled it short outside off, got across and slapped it towards midwicket, stole a quick single to keep strike for the final over
low full toss, pushed wide of extra cover, just the single
banged it short on the off, goes for the pull, misses
short outside off, run down to third man to give Taylor the strike
slower one bowled short, turned his wrists and played it down to fine leg
slower one bowled really short outside off, tried to upper cut it but couldn't make contact, Mills continues to be impressive
pitched it up and he drilled it down the ground towards long-on for a couple

inn2.comm: short of a good length on the off, rocks back and drops it into the off side
New Zealand are away, a bit of width and Guptill punches it between cover and point for a couple
dropped it short on middle and leg, Guptill shuffled across and tried to turn it fine, it went off the thigh
back of a length on the off, rocks back and knosks it down into the off side
too much width, short and wide, he flays it over point for three runs, it slowed down in the outfield
shortish outside off and he chases it but can't connect, slashes hard but misses out
starts off by overstepping, was pitched up and it nipped back in, went for the drive but missed, he has another chance, freehit coming up
in the slot, pitched it up outside off and this went the other way, made room and caressed it past extra cover for a boundary
good length just outside off, pushed into the off side off the front foot
picked the gap again, back of a length, rocks back and punches it through the covers for three more runs, a fluent start this
straying on the pads, he flicks it fine but there is a fielder in the deep, he runs across and keeps them to one
shortish on the off, punched towards cover from the crease
lovely shot, good length and he just struck that confidently through the line, Sibanda played a similar shot early in the Zimbabwe innings, timed to perfection and it beats mid-on
steps out of the crease and pulls that shortish delivery wide of midwicket for a couple, didn't time it too well
short of a good length on the off, punched off the back foot to cover
angled in towards middle, he gets across to turn it to midwicket
timed it well, was a slow full toss, worked it away wristily through square leg into the deep for two runs
shortish on the off, punched it wide of mid-off for a quick single
short of a good length, stands tall and punches it towards mid-on
targeting Jarvis here, bowled it around a good length, he charged down the track, took it from a length and whacked it over mid-on for a boundary
poor delivery, a juicy half-volley on the pads, flicked it over midwicket, just a chip and it flew off his bat
too straight, shortish on middle, turned past square leg for a couple of runs
a slight leading edge, Jarvis bowled that full on middle and Nicol was aiming for midwicket but he appeared to check his shot at the last moment there
short and down the leg side, it makes for a wide
full on the off, gets forward, to the pitch, and plays it to cover
bowlde it on a good length on the off, pushed down towards mid-on
gets forward and plays it firmly wide of mid-off for a single, extra cover got a hand to it and kept it down to one with a dive to his right
slower one bowled on a good length on the off, defended back towards the bowler
held it back a bit, chopped it wide of point for a single
bowling at the pads, turned away towards fine leg for a single
short fine leg is in the circle and those are easy pickings for Nicol, short on middle and leg and he worked it off his hips really fine
banged it short but down the leg side, an appeal for a catch by the bowler as Nicol went for the pull but it was more for avoiding a wide call
back of a length on middle, gets on the back foot and taps it to the bowler
straying on the pads and Guptill will feel he missed out there, tried to flick it fine but was struck on the pads
bowlde it full on the off, drove it down firmly but straight to mid-on
fuller ball on middle, flicked to midwicket
Jarvis is struggling with his line here, doles out a gift on the pads and Nicol is only too happy to glance it down fine
held it back this time and pitched it around a good length, Nicol came out of the crease and defended it with bat close to pad back to the bowler
in the channel outside off, gets his line right this time as the batsman lets it go but it's a no-ball, he's overstepped, so a freehit coming

caught off a freehit, a full toss and he gets a top edge as he tries to whip that over square leg, it's caught by the fielder at short fine leg but by the time he returns a throw, they've taken two, 50 up in quick time
good length outside off, holds its line but he opts to let it go
fullish on middle and it's driven firmlby back to the bowler who does well to block it on his follow-through
straying in line, on the pads, walks across and flicks it behind short fine leg for a couple of runs
that took the batsman by surprise a bit, a bouncer and he was caught in two minds, but backed away at the right time
back of a length, stands tall and punches it straight to extra cover
round the wicket and angles it down the leg side, called a wide
flighted on middle, pushed towards deep midwicket for a single
quicker through the air, short outside off and holds its line, tries to open the face but misses
angling it towards middle, stretches forward and defends it to the bowler
angling it towards middle, defended solidly down the pitch once again
pushed past Price for a single to mid-off, the fielder there didn't pick it upo cleanly
struck on the pads but that was going down leg, tossed up on leg stump and he played a little outside the line to that one
shortish on the off, crunched to point off the back foot
short of a good length, gets back and punches it to mid-off
not as much width as he would have liked, a little too close to cut, chopped it down to point
too short and he seizes the chance, rocks back and pulls it hard through the vacant square leg region for a boundary
short outside off again, chopped off the back foot to point
goodish length this time, right on middle, pushed back towards the bowler
